                " \nSOUTH AFRICAN NATIONAL BIODIVERSITY INSTITUTE (SANBI)\n ",
                " \n \nTECHNICIAN: SPECIES RECOVERY\nReference Number: GKBC/2023/012\n \nThe South African National Biodiversity Institute (SANBI) is looking for a self-motivated individual to effectively co-ordinate the botanical restoration component of the Millennium Seed Bank Partnership (MSBP) Karoo Biome Extension Programme, responding to the Illegal plant poaching crisis facing South Africa. The successful candidate will conduct research and implement best practices species recovery protocols for threatened species in the Karoo and Fynbos Biomes, develop species recovery templates/guides for threatened species, and implement species recovery projects in collaboration with Botanical Gardens, land managers, nature reserves and private landowners.\n\n \nThis position requires a Grade 12, job specific qualification, or equivalent qualification at NQF 4 with 5 years of work experience in the relevant field or a national diploma in Horticulture, Natural Sciences, or equivalent qualification at NQF 6 with 3 years of work experience in the relevant field. An advanced diploma or a degree in Horticulture, Natural Sciences, or equivalent qualification at NQF 7 will be an added advantage.\n \nThe following competencies are required for the candidate to be successful in this position. plant identification skills; advanced knowledge and experience in species recovery and seed collection will be advantageous; demonstrate a high level of attention to detail, and exceptional accuracy with capturing data; knowledge of plant diversity and taxonomy; excellent written and verbal communication skills, excellent planning, organising, problem solving and analytical skills; highly motivated individual that has an ability to work under pressure with a diverse team whilst being quality, cost and safety conscious; and advanced computer literacy and must be proficient in MS Excel; The possession of a valid driver\u2019s licence with at least one-year practical driving experience will be required.\n \nKey Performance Responsibilities include:\nSpecies Recovery planning and implementation;\nConservation, Research and Development;\nMillennium Seed Bank Partnership Team Support;\nSupport to integrated conservation activities and,\nProject administration.\n \nApplication procedure:\n1) An application form must accompany the CV together with a letter motivating why the applicant should be favourably considered for this position, and certified qualifications confirming that the minimum qualifications are met (applicants lacking evidence of meeting minimum qualifications and relevant experience will not be considered).\n2) A competency test will be conducted as part of the selection process.\n3) Applicants must also provide the full names, addresses and telephone numbers and if possible e-mail addresses of at least three referees.\n4) Failure to submit the requested information and reference number shall result in your application not being considered.\n \nPersonal Information will be processed by SANBI for purposes of assessing your suitability for the advertised position. SANBI may also share your personal information including special personal information with service providers or third parties, both within the Republic of South Africa and in other jurisdictions, to carry out verification of qualifications and other necessary documents, background and reference checks, competency assessment tests, and criminal record checks. In this regard, by virtue of your application, you acknowledge that SANBI\u2019s authorised verification agent(s) and service providers will access your personal information including special personal information to conduct background screening, verification of qualifications and other necessary documents, reference checks, competency assessment tests, and criminal record checks. For more information, kindly refer to SANBI\u2019s website.\nPersons with disabilities are encouraged to apply. SANBI reserves the right not to fill this position. All applications will be considered with the understanding that, in terms of the SANBI Employment Equity Plan, preference will be given to candidates from the designated groups.\n \nContact Ms Zena Appollis on Tel: +27 (0)21 7998647 for any queries for purposes of clarity. Applications consisting of the completed application form, motivation letter, a concise CV, and certified qualifications are to be submitted via an e-mail to recruitmentct@sanbi.org.za\n \nPostal applications must be addressed to:\nDeputy Director: Human Resources Operations\nSouth African National Biodiversity Institute\nPrivate Bag X7\nClaremont\n7700\n \nCandidates are expected to be available for selection interviews on a date and time as determined by SANBI. If no response has been received within 30 days of the closing date, candidates must consider their applications unsuccessful.\n \nApplication form\nCloses: Wednesday, 29 November 2023\nJob type: Fixed-Term Contract ending 31 May 2025\nSalary: R241 485.00 plus 37% in lieu of benefits\nLocation: Cape Town\n \n \n \n \n ",
                "HUMAN RESOURCES ADMINISTRATOR\nReference Number: HR/003/2023\n \nThe South African National Biodiversity Institute (SANBI) is looking for a self-motivated individual to attend to response handling of job applications, administrative matters related to, but not limited to, recruitment, selection, and appointment activities including other human resources related administrative services.\nThis position requires a Grade 10, Job Specific Qualification, or equivalent qualification at NQF 2 with 5 years of work experience in the relevant field, OR Grade 12, Job Specific Qualification, or equivalent qualification at NQF 4 with 4 years of work experience in the relevant.  A Higher Education Qualification, Job Specific Qualification or equivalent qualification at NQF 5 will be an added advantage.\nThe following competencies are required for the candidate to be successful in this position: comprehensive knowledge and experience about legislation, policies, procedures, processes, practices, systems, and frameworks pertaining to human resources management; proven ability to work with diverse team and under pressure whilst being quality, cost, and safety conscious; attention to details, good records keeping, filing of documents, information management and processing; ability to keep confidential matters, handle confidential information and deal with HR clients in a professional and service oriented manner;  advanced planning, organizing, interpersonal, and problem solving, project and event management skills; excellent communication skills (both verbal and written); excellent computer literacy and experience in the application of software tools including (MS Word, MS Project, PowerPoint, Excel, Internet and Outlook) will be advantageous. The possession of a valid driver\u2019s licence with at least one-year practical driving experience and a willingness to travel will be advantageous.\n \nKey Performance Responsibilities include:\nAttend to response handling of applications, data capturing, and processing of job applications according to the job adverts;\nCoordinate and assist with logistical arrangements for the shortlisting, skills test writing, interviews, meetings, competency based assessments, and on boarding processes; and\nAssist with recruitment, selection, appointment and other human resources related administrative services.\n \nApplication procedure:\n1) An application form must accompany the CV together with a letter motivating why the applicant should be favourably considered for this position, and certified qualifications confirming that the minimum qualifications are met (applicants lacking evidence of meeting minimum qualifications and relevant experience will not be considered).\n2) A competency test may be conducted as part of the selection process.\n3) Applicants must also provide the full names, addresses and telephone numbers and if possible e-mail addresses of at least three referees.\n4) Failure to submit the requested information and reference number shall result in your application not being considered.\n \nPersonal Information will be processed by SANBI for purposes of assessing your suitability for the advertised position. SANBI may also share your personal information including special personal information with service providers or third parties, both within the Republic of South Africa and in other jurisdictions, to carry out verification of qualifications and other necessary documents, background and reference checks, competency assessment tests, and criminal record checks. In this regard, by virtue of your application, you acknowledge that SANBI\u2019s authorised verification agent(s) and service providers will access your personal information including special personal information to conduct background screening, verification of qualifications and other necessary documents, reference checks, competency assessment tests, and criminal record checks. For more information, kindly refer to SANBI\u2019s website.\n \nPersons with disabilities are encouraged to apply. SANBI reserves the right not to fill this position. All applications will be considered with the understanding that, in terms of the SANBI Employment Equity Plan, preference will be given to candidates from the designated groups.\n \nContact Ms Martha Pilusa on 012 843 5252 for any queries related to seeking clarity on this position. Applications consisting of the completed application form, motivation letter, a concise CV, and certified qualifications must be submitted via an e-mail to recruitmentpta@sanbi.org.za\n \nPostal applications must be addressed to:\nAssistant Director: Human Resources\nSouth African National Biodiversity Institute\nPrivate Bag X101\nPretoria\n0001\nCandidates are expected to be available for selection interviews on a date and time as determined by SANBI. If no response has been received within 30 days of the closing date, candidates must consider their applications unsuccessful.\n \nApplication form\nCloses: Thursday, 30 November 2023\nJob type: 6 month Fixed-term contract\nSalary: R202 233.00 plus 37% in lieu of benefits\nLocation: Pretoria"
